# .bit Language Schema

## Structure
Lines are indented with 4 spaces. # starts a group. ## starts a subgroup.

## Tasks
Tasks use bracket status markers, indented under groups:
    [!] Pending task (not started)
    [o] In-progress task
    [x] Completed task
Labeled tasks: [A!] Design API    [B!] Build API
Assigned tasks: [!] Fix auth :@agent    [!] Review PR :@user:alice

## Key-Value Fields
Indented under any node:
    title: "Build the calculator"
    priority: 1
    status: :active
    tags: [:backend, :api]

## Entities & Schemas
Define entity schemas with field types:
    define:@Task
        title: "Untitled"
        state: :todo/:in_progress/:done

    define:@Sprint
        name string !
        start_date timestamp
        points int

Field sigils: ! required, ^ indexed, @ timestamp, # int, ## float, ? bool, [] list, {} json, -> relation

## Mutations
Create or update entity instances:
    mutate:@Task:build-api
        title: "Build the API"
        state: :in_progress

## Supertags & References
    @Task:abc123          typed entity reference
    @abc123               bare reference
    #urgent               tag
    #project/backend      hierarchical tag

## Flows
Dependency graphs between labeled tasks:
    flow:
        A --> B
        B --> C

## Checks and Validate Suites
Use check: for executable expectations and validate name: as a named suite
that groups related checks. A task is not done just because files changed; it is
done when the relevant checks pass and receipts are fresh.

## Code Blocks
    ```python
    def hello():
        print("hello")
    ```

## Tools Reference

Bit CLI (use first and often):
- $Bit.parse(source) — parse .bit text, returns AST or errors
- $Bit.index(source) — extract tasks/groups/entities, validate structure
- $Bit.render(ast) — render AST back to .bit text
- $Bit.schemas(source) — extract entity schemas with field types
- $Bit.mutate(source) — apply mutations, build data store

Memory:
- $Memory.remember(content) — persist learnings across sessions
- $Memory.recall(query) — retrieve relevant past context

Files & Shell:
- $File.read(path) / $File.write(path, content)
- $Shell.run(command)
